quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  7,38,"He said{1}, “Enter with the communities of unseen beings{2}and humans who have gone into the Fire before you.” Every time a community entered, it cursed its sister-community till, when they were all in it, the last of them said about the first of them, “Our Lord, these are the ones who led us astray, so bring upon them double punishment in the Fire.” He said, “Each will have double, but <span class=""h"">you<sup foot_note=""80063"" class=""qiraat"">3</sup> </span><span class=""h"">know</span>not.”",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.The Arabic word used is jinnwhich are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.
  7,39,"And the first of them said to the last of them, “Thus you had no advantage over us, so taste the punishment on account of what you used to earn.”"
  7,40,"Indeed, those who disbelieved in Our signs and were too arrogant to accept them—the gates of the heaven<span class=""h"">will not be widely opened<sup foot_note=""80064"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>for them, nor will they enter the Garden<i class=""s"">(of Paradise) </i>until the camel{2}passes through the eye of the needle. And thus We repay the criminals.",footnotes:2:The Arabic word used is jamalwhich also means ‘thick rope’.
  7,41,"For them is Hell as a resting place, and above them are sheets of fire. And thus We repay the unjust<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>."
  7,42,"But those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds—We never task any self beyond its capacity—those are the fellows of the Garden<i class=""s"">(of Paradise) </i>; therein they abide."
  7,43,"And We removed<a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a>whatever malice was within their chests; rivers flow beneath them. And they said, “Praise be to Allah who has guided us to this, <span class=""h"">for<sup foot_note=""80066"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>never would we have been guided had Allah not guided us; most surely, the messengers of our Lord did come with the truth.” And it was called out to them, “This is the Garden<i class=""s"">(of Paradise) </i>you are made to inherit on account of what you used to do.”"
